    "created_at": "2025-05-01T23:32:33Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-05-01T23:32:33Z",
    "body": "I fixed this manually by adding a guard variable to the `eval \"$(starship init bash)\"`. So, instead of just doing the `eval`, I do:\n\n```\nif [ -z \"$__STARSHIP_ALREADY_INIT\" ]; then\n    eval \"$(starship init bash)\"\n    export __STARSHIP_ALREADY_INIT=1\nfi\n```",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
